    schema1:description "Anneke is a physician who specialised in clinical genetics and is professor of genomic medicine and consultant in clinical genetics at the University of Oxford (since 2021). She leads a research group extending across universities of Oxford and Southampton that explores the clinical ethical, legal and societal issues (CELS) involved in developments in genomics and big data within medicine."@en ;
